name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: The TN General Assembly will convene for a special legislative session on January 19, 2021, to address urgent issues facing our students and schools in the 2021-22 school year including learning loss, funding, accountability, literacy, and teacher pay.  https://t.co/8dpU9mG8PX

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: I’m calling on the legislature to join us in addressing these serious issues so we can equip our hardworking educators and districts with the resources and supports they need to set our students on the path to success.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: Even before the virus hit, and despite years of improvement, too many of our state’s students were still unable to read on grade level.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: We know that the COVID-19 pandemic has caused immense disruption for Tennessee’s students, educators, and districts, and the challenges they face must be addressed urgently.  https://t.co/8dpU9mG8PX

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: Lower taxes lead to job creation, prosperous communities, and more money in the pockets of hardworking Tennesseans. We're proud to be recognized as one of the lowest tax burden states in the country while maintaining a high level of service to our customers, the people of TN.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: WATCH: This morning, I joined @AmericaNewsroom on @FoxNews to discuss the Christmas Day bombing in Nashville, the heroic @MNPDNashville officers who saved countless lives, and our emergency declaration request to @POTUS.  https://t.co/armUf7ywL2

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: Thank you, Officer Brenna Hosey, Officer Tyler Luellen, Officer Michael Sipos, Officer Amanda Topping, Officer James Wells, and Sergeant Timothy Miller

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: We are forever grateful for the heroic @MNPDNashville officers who saved countless lives on Christmas morning.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: Tune in as I join @AmericaNewsroom live on @FoxNews at 8 CT

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: Thank you, Senator @MarshaBlackburn. We appreciate the support shown by our Tennessee delegation.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: I have requested an emergency declaration from @POTUS  to support ongoing efforts and relief.  https://t.co/7vwrvN1FBw

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: We are thankful to the @FBI and the @ATFHQ for leading the investigation and remain in close communication with them.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: The swift action of @MNPDNashville and local law enforcement saved lives and I commend their courage.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: This morning I toured the site of the bombing. The damage is shocking and it is a miracle that no residents were killed. @MariaLeeTN and I continue to pray for those who sustained injuries from the blast.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: We are thankful for the prayers and encouragement over the last several days.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: Sharing personal news before we discuss the ongoing investigation of the bombing in downtown Nashville. I have tested negative for COVID-19, continue to feel well and have completed the quarantine period. @MariaLeeTN has fully recovered and is doing well.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: We will supply all of the resources needed to determine what happened and who was responsible. Please join @MariaLeeTN and me in praying for those who were injured and we thank all of our first responders who acted so quickly this morning.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: Early this morning, an explosion occurred in downtown Nashville around Second Avenue and Commerce Street. Federal, state and local law enforcement partners are on the scene to investigate what we believe was an intentional act.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: .@MariaLeeTN and I pray that Peace and Hope are found in the midst of this day. Merry Christmas and God bless our great state.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: On this Christmas Day, we reflect on all the ways the Lord has carried our state this year, even through pain and struggles. Eternal hope remains steadfast, because of the birth of Him who we celebrate today.  https://t.co/ZAC4ukFn9z

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: This week is ordinarily a time when families across the state are gathering to celebrate. Unfortunately, these are not ordinary times. Our state is ground zero for a surge in COVID-19 and we need Tennesseans to their part - Wear a mask - Only gather with your immediate household  https://t.co/7cT71yWMqI

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: We must do all that we can to blunt this surge and keep more Tennesseans from getting sick. Wear a mask and only gather with your immediate household during the holidays.  https://t.co/WQTvT8gs4A

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: Executive Order 73 extends the state of emergency and provisions that have been critical to our COVID-19 response. Also, I have issued EO 71 and 72 to extend electronic government meetings and remote notarization provisions.  https://t.co/oKPVLGIwtw  https://t.co/CJmG5qRHiT

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: Thank you, Dr. Piercey, for administering the Moderna vaccine to frontline workers in Rutherford County yesterday.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: A quick update to let you know that @MariaLeeTN is feeling better and I continue to have no symptoms.   The next few weeks are critical for our state and we need every Tennessean to do their part.  - Wear a mask - Only gather with your immediate household  https://t.co/SJj8S1CrqZ

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: We have seen firsthand that holiday gatherings and extended time indoors have been the principal driver in spreading COVID-19 like wildfire. TN cannot sustain a similar surge, and we need Tennesseans to do their part - Wear a mask - Only gather with your immediate household  https://t.co/sPHmyh2bCj

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: Executive Order 70  https://t.co/ly2CuE8X1Z

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: A vaccine is an effective tool in our fight against COVID-19, but it will be limited for some time. The most powerful thing that every Tennessean can do today is using these simple, smart habits.  https://t.co/utxNkqDIet

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: We can and must turn the tide on the rate of COVID-19 cases in our state and we need every Tennessean to hear that message loud and clear.   Your decision to wear a mask today may be the very thing that makes a difference in the weeks ahead.  https://t.co/wTFKxBBZnx

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: As safe and effective COVID-19 vaccines arrive in our state, Tennesseans can stay up-to-date with our most recent plans and find FAQs at  https://t.co/EFG855DAh2  https://t.co/lXBatQtJCG

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: While we celebrate the arrival of a safe, effective vaccine, it will be limited for some time. The most powerful antidote that every Tennessean can take today is practicing simple, smart habits like wearing a mask.  https://t.co/rdXskG8wiw

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: Our state is getting sicker by the day, and this vaccine will not cure selfishness and indifference. I believe Tennesseans have a tremendous capacity to make responsible decisions, and we need you to wear a mask and consider alternate holiday gatherings.  https://t.co/3K3HSCTs3H

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: The first allocations of both the Moderna and Pfizer COVID-19 vaccines in Tennessee will be provided to individuals qualifying for Phase 1a1.  https://t.co/CDGIAL5F3w  https://t.co/B7tUriaEde

tweet: Yesterday, the @US_FDA announced that vials of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine, which are labeled as containing five doses, may include enough of the vaccine to provide 6-7 doses. TN may have as many as 11,000 more doses to provide than originally expected.

name: Gov. Bill Lee
tweet: We anticipate 115,000 doses of the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine to arrive at our 95 county health departments on 12/21.  https://t.co/oVwpw6PNJS  https://t.co/PysJV6j4PM
